message.content: cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. The paper deals with Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new setting for VQA, which involves developing models that can answer questions about unseen compositions of seen concepts, which requires artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Hence, cs.AI is also a likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates several existing VQA models, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as deep learning, making cs.LG a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper analyzes the distribution of questions and answers in the VQA dataset, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, making cs.IR a possible sub-category as well.
